body:
Hi! I have re-created a minimal reproducible example:

```rust
trait A {
    type F;
    fn new() -> Self;
}

struct S {}

impl A for S {
    type F = fn() -> i32;

    fn new() -> Self {
        S {}
    }
}

fn test<T: A>(_: T::F) -> T {
    T::new()
}

fn main() {
    // Works fine
    test::<S>(|| 0);
    // Doesn't compile
    let _: S = test(|| 0);
}
```

I expected that the compiler treats both type hints equally `test::<S>(|| 0);` and `let _: S = test(|| 0);`.

Instead,  the second invocation fails to compile (under `1.57.0` and `nightly`):

```bash
error[E0271]: type mismatch resolving `<S as A>::F == [closure@src/main.rs:220:21: 220:25]`
   --> src/main.rs:220:16
    |
220 |     let _: S = test(|| 0);
    |                ^^^^^^^^^^ type mismatch resolving `<S as A>::F == [closure@src/main.rs:220:21: 220:25]`
    |
note: expected this to be `fn() -> i32`
   --> src/main.rs:205:14
    |
205 |     type F = fn() -> i32;
    |              ^^^^^^^^^^^
    = note: expected fn pointer `fn() -> i32`
                  found closure `[closure@src/main.rs:220:21: 220:25]`
```
